    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - INSTALL - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The countershaft must be installed first.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure the synchronizer cups on the mainshaft front end stay in position as the mainshaft is
                    lowered into the case.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The rear bearing cover is marked for proper installation.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a sling or rope around the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026g9">Figure 169</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026g9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026g9" filename="../figg13/G13026G9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 169. Position Sling or Rope Around Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully lower the mainshaft into the case while guiding the output shaft through the rear
                case bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">For the FS-5205 model, install the mainshaft rear outer bearing race in the output shaft
                bearing bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h0">Figure 170</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026h0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026h0" filename="../figg13/G13026H0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 170. Install Mainshaft Rear Outer Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the output shaft bearing cap oil seal outer diameter with Loctite 242 or equivalent (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h1">Figure 171</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026h1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026h1" filename="../figg13/G13026H1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 171. Coat Output Shaft Bearing Cap Oil Seal Outer Diameter With Loctite 242 and Install
                    Oil Seal
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the oil seal with a flanged driver (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h1">Figure 171</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the output shaft bearing race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h2">Figure 172</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026h2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026h2" filename="../figg13/G13026H2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 172. Install Output Shaft Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Temporarily position shims on the rear bearing mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h3">Figure 173</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026h3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026h3" filename="../figg13/G13026H3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 173. Temporarily Position Shims, Position Rear Bearing Cover Over Shims, and Install
                    Retaining Nuts
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the rear bearing cover over the shims (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h3">Figure 173</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining nuts and tighten to 60 to 70 ft-lbs. (81 to 95 N&#8226; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h3">Figure 173</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
